  "texts": [
    "In the medical domain, TL is frequently employed due to the scarcity of extensively annotated massive amounts of medical datasets comparable to the ImageNet database 62.",
    "In this study, three pre-trained CNNs including AlexNet 52, ResNet50 53, and DenseNet201 54 that were previously trained on the ImageNet dataset are constructed.",
    "TL is utilized to modify the output layer of convolutional CNNs to have 9 and 8 nodes, respectively, matching the number of categories in the NCT-CRC-HE-100 K dataset and the Kather_texture_2016_image_tiles dataset.",
    "The augmented pictures generated in the prior phase are subsequently employed to retrain the pre-trained CNNs by modifying certain hyperparameters of the CNNs, such as minibatch size, learning rate, number of epochs, and validation rate.",
    "Further elaboration on the hyper-parameter finetuning will be provided in Sect."
  ],
